    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves Gradation 1 against a required level of 2; this gap is accepted given the COU is explicitly scoped to the single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending condition and no extrapolation beyond that condition is claimed. Uncertainty quantification via comprehensive Monte Carlo sampling across all model inputs has been completed and prediction intervals are reported. Overall credibility is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion. The model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) demonstrates consistent agreement with experimental data across both laboratories, and the E/uval metric is below 1.96 for all primary QoIs.",
